		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It might be simpler to say it's the final byte in the opcode string. As it would have been read last from the bus the cartridge is on. I believe that basically says the same thing everyone else has said in a most simple way. Also, I don't really think any licensed game would rely on open bus returning a specific value.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
